153
00:14:47,464 --> 00:14:52,849
And so, plan a starts at under state law section I think it's 4045 44.

154
00:14:53,349 --> 00:14:54,410
And there's a whole.

155
00:14:59,657 --> 00:15:03,460
provision, there are several sections above that that cover all the forms of government.

156
00:15:05,282 --> 00:15:20,175
That sort of include things like the mayor signing off on certain things, forms of government, like Plan A. There's a whole section of state law about elections, about the operations of schools.

157
00:15:20,635 --> 00:15:20,935
So again,

158
00:15:23,380 --> 00:15:30,144
And communities have certain control over how those things operate specifically in their own community.

159
00:15:30,164 --> 00:15:38,228
But Medford has not chosen to sort of, under the charter at least, it has not chosen to exercise that authority.

160
00:15:38,608 --> 00:15:47,113
Therefore, the default is to the rather limited regulations in state law.

161
00:15:47,133 --> 00:15:50,595
I don't know if Marilyn or Frank want to chime in a little bit on this point.

162
00:15:57,878 --> 00:15:59,119
I'll jump in.

163
00:16:00,020 --> 00:16:02,981
Just kind of jumping on where Anthony left off.

164
00:16:04,022 --> 00:16:07,384
It may depend on what the issue is.

165
00:16:07,424 --> 00:16:21,193
You'd look to the statutes, case law perhaps, and your ordinances may address some of the issues depending on what the topic is or the question is.

166
00:16:22,454 --> 00:16:25,656
The ordinances obviously are much easier to change and

167
00:16:26,870 --> 00:16:36,799
can come and go, whereas the charter is a much firmer foundation upon which your local government is established and maintained.

168
00:16:36,819 --> 00:16:36,859
OK.

169
00:16:38,381 --> 00:16:40,983
All right, thank you.

