178
00:17:32,103 --> 00:17:36,466
How would that differ from kind of making amendments to it?

179
00:17:36,906 --> 00:17:38,708
Do we have to like recreate the wheel?

180
00:17:39,905 --> 00:17:45,649
can any of these sections kind of be filled in and what would that process look like?

181
00:17:45,870 --> 00:17:48,412
And can you walk us through that?

182
00:17:51,454 --> 00:18:06,305
So I think the short answer is that amendments to certain, well, first of all, you don't have to, what you've got in front of you is an example of sort of things that we would recommend a community put into its charter.

183
00:18:06,325 --> 00:18:06,546
And again,

184
00:18:07,732 --> 00:18:17,835
I think part of it, especially in Medford's case, is in terms of readability or things for your regular citizen to look at and say, I know how my local government operates.

185
00:18:20,736 --> 00:18:31,518
You don't necessarily have to adopt any of the things or even structure your charter in the way that is suggested or at least put forth in that particular memo.

186
00:18:33,239 --> 00:18:36,220
Having said that, any change, let's say you wanted to

187
00:18:39,710 --> 00:18:53,116
just add one of those sections from the charter or from the memo and sort of fill that out, or at least take your existing charter and structure it in the way so suggested.

188
00:18:55,337 --> 00:19:07,943
Whether it's a wholesale change or a change to an individual section, it'll have to go through the same process of being submitted to the city council, voted on, sent to the state house for approval,

189
00:19:08,323 --> 00:19:14,706
and then back to the city for back to the voters.

190
00:19:17,988 --> 00:19:18,668
Okay, thank you.

191
00:19:18,868 --> 00:19:19,169
