198
00:20:18,350 --> 00:20:23,412
So I just want to have some clarification about that section in particular.

199
00:20:23,432 --> 00:20:28,493
Would it be not relevant 20 years after the charter changes are all passed?

200
00:20:29,754 --> 00:20:30,974
Or am I misunderstanding that?

201
00:20:34,177 --> 00:20:39,259
So Marilyn, you can fill this out for us, but the short answer is yes.

202
00:20:40,380 --> 00:20:49,064
The transition section would really be filled out based upon the things that you do or don't decide to change or how you decide to make the modifications.

203
00:20:49,224 --> 00:20:57,528
And then the transition section would just focus on the things through your discussion as a committee and the things that you learn from your hearings.

204
00:21:00,229 --> 00:21:01,450
You may need some time for the

205
00:21:02,502 --> 00:21:04,443
organization to adjust to the new structure.

206
00:21:04,843 --> 00:21:16,188
And they would only last until the transition period is over, however you determine, whenever you determine to put that sunset time to be, or the city, really the city council ultimately.

207
00:21:18,489 --> 00:21:22,791
What's an instance of like something that's needed to go into a transition section previously?

208
00:21:22,811 --> 00:21:32,115
Well, one example is the budget process.

209
00:21:33,155 --> 00:21:41,637
say that you adopt this provision for an annual budget meeting that you don't have now.

210
00:21:43,978 --> 00:21:56,722
And the charter passes, but the budget, the charter is adopted by the voters in November, but the charter process, the budget process is already underway.

211
00:21:57,322 --> 00:22:00,703
So the transition provision might provide that that would take effect

212
00:22:01,443 --> 00:22:04,185
in the budget in the following fiscal year.

